channel.description:
I try to create a tag cloud. I've seen in the `twentytwenty-theme` and in other themes, that you use a function like this, to get tags:
const allTags = state.source.tag; const tags = post.tags && post.tags.map(tagId => allTags[tagId]);
I tried to implement something similar, but it did not wanted to work. My WP site has 785 Tags at the moment. If I type `console.log(Object.keys(allTags).length);` then I get a number like 182. This number is growing as I visit different pages. If I try: `state.source.tag[someID]`, than it's working for tags, appearing on my frontpage, but if I write a TagID, what is not related to posts on my frontpage, then I get `undefined`. So how could I create a TagCloud?
